            <div type="translation">
                <p>Mother of God, Eleousa</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The depiction of the Virgin is directly related to the depiction of Christ on the southwestern panel. Is essentially a dialogue between Virgin and Christ. Virgin the Merciful addresses Christ pleading him to show mercy to the humankind. This representation goes back to the Comnenian art and can be found also in other churches in Cyprus like Panagia tou Arakos at Lagoudera village. It is worth noting that this specific depiction of the Virgin in Cyprus is entitled Ἡ Ἐλεοῦσα, while elsewhere the epithet used is Ἡ Παράκλησις. </p>
            </div>
